doc: update contribute.html

Fixes issue 4582.

* mentioned hg upload.
* added section on hg file.
* added small mention about being inside $GOROOT.
* added hg revert @NNNN
* reorganise the hg submit section for the common case of a non committer.
* made the Copyright section h2
* added note about leaving copyright years unchanged.

really good, i think most of the necessary content is covered. the remaining codereview sub-commands: 1. hg gofmt (very useful, should be documented) 2. hg undo (rarely used, but sometimes useful) 3. hg release-apply (even more rarely used, could be left out) https://codereview.appspot.com/7278047/diff/6003/doc/contribute.html File doc/contribute.html (right): https://codereview.appspot.com/7278047/diff/6003/doc/contribute.html#newcode506 doc/contribute.html:506: (Anyone can run clpatch to try a change that i think we can completely remove stuff about 'hg submit' and instead give more emphasis on 'hg clp', as the former is only usable by a few while the latter is useful to every Go user who wishes to try out a change.

LGTM https://codereview.appspot.com/7278047/diff/20001/doc/contribute.html File doc/contribute.html (right): https://codereview.appspot.com/7278047/diff/20001/doc/contribute.html#newcode303 doc/contribute.html:303: to add somefile to CL 99999, and use s/ use// https://codereview.appspot.com/7278047/diff/20001/doc/contribute.html#newcode411 doc/contribute.html:411: Creating or uploading the change uploads a copy of the diff to the code review server, s/or/and/ Creating the change with "hg change" does not upload the diff. https://codereview.appspot.com/7278047/diff/20001/doc/contribute.html#newcode438 doc/contribute.html:438: If your change relates to an open issue, it is recommended that you add a s/it is recommended that you/please/ https://codereview.appspot.com/7278047/diff/20001/doc/contribute.html#newcode439 doc/contribute.html:439: comment to the issue announcing your proposed fix.
